        <div class="relative group cursor-pointer lightbox-trigger">
          <img 
            src="/image/fereshteh.jpg" 
            alt="Fereshteh Shabestani"
            class="w-full h-[600px] object-cover object-top transition-transform duration-500 group-hover:scale-105"
          />
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/50 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-white text-lg">Click to enlarge</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Fereshteh Shabestani</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Class of ELT 2022-2023</p>
            </div>
            <span class="bg-secondary text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm">Pastry Chef</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Fereshteh Shabestani became a pastry chef at Red Shores shortly after she left the ELT class. She appreciated the portfolio she built in the class and felt prepared when she went to the interview.
          </p>
          <div class="border-l-4 border-secondary pl-4 italic text-gray-600">
            "Now she is the pastry chef at Dalvay-By-the-Sea Hotel where she creates delightful desserts to satisfy and impress all the guests at this historic hotel in the PEI National Park."
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Jin Jia Story -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="relative group cursor-pointer lightbox-trigger">
          <img 
            src="/image/jin-jia.jpg" 
            alt="Jin Jia in front of Jane's Dumplings"
            class="w-full h-[600px] object-cover object-top transition-transform duration-500 group-hover:scale-105"
          />
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/50 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-white text-lg">Click to enlarge</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Jin Jia</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Class of ELT 2018-2019</p>
            </div>
            <span class="bg-secondary text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm">Entrepreneur</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            I'll never forget my time in Beverley's ELT Hospitality Class. I often helped a classmate who struggled with challenging reading materials, doing my best to support his understanding. I didn't think much of it—it was just a small act of kindness repeated over time. To my surprise, Beverley noticed and presented me with the "Extra Mile" award. Her recognition meant a great deal to me. It planted a seed that grew into a belief I carry with me to this day: always go the extra mile.<br/><br/>
            That small moment of encouragement helped shape a much bigger dream—to build a meaningful life and career in my new country. This mindset has been essential as my husband and I built our businesses—MoJi-fast Technology Ltd., a solar energy system installation company, and Jane's Dumplings, our restaurant. The English skills, confidence, and positive attitude I gained in the ELT Hospitality Class have helped us overcome countless challenges as newcomers to Canada.<br/><br/>
            Starting a business in a new country is never easy, but the foundation I built through the ELT Hospitality Class gave me the courage to turn challenges into opportunities—and dreams into reality.
          </p>
